			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This is to Dianeas that posted about Paladins getting awsome weapons...<BR>
<BR>
Soulfire - 23/45?  Blows.  You gota do a big frigen quest for it and basically your questing for the look, not the item.  Cause the item sucks, the look is cool.  One can camp Xalgoz in Kaesoria for a few hours and get a 23/40ish weapon. Heh<BR>
<BR>
Fiery Avenger - Gota kill two dragons, get the rare drop off them (two books), kill the most powerfull necromancer on norrath, then get to the 4th or 5th island in PoS - LOL.  Obtainable?  Not really...  Good weapon tho, even tho you can camp some lamer kunark items for a day or two and get something better.<BR>
<BR>
Ghoulbane - Camped mine for 30 hours and got it, still a good weapon.  <BR>
<BR>
Sword of Mourning - One of the best weapons we have, off high level mob in the crypt in sebilis.  Very good weapon<BR>
<BR>
Intes Sword of Death - Was a joke by the Dev team, they didnt think anyone would kill the mob in the PoA from the guy that has the Fiery Avenger quest.  Does not drop anymore, there's only 1 - 2 of them and i think they were nerfed.<BR>
<BR>
(You forgot one, Halycon Broadsword which is a once a week drop off the Ancient Wyvyern in Skyfire)  Of course it's all random, but it's about as rare as a once-a-week drop.  <BR>
<BR>
Ok, we got all those items, We get a total of two class only items in kunark.  Rangers get about 12, shadowknights get about 9, warriors get about 8-10, bards get a few, even casters get a few (2 or three, frost dagger, rod of anhiliation, few others i believe).  Paladins get two.  Point number two...  Shadowknight MOSS (mace of shadowed souls) drops in CoM, and its' very common, almost all shadowknights on Xegony either have this, or the deathbringers rod (i think that's what it's called, it's 30/40 i do know that).  They also have the 'urn', i forget the name of the weapon but it's like 24/36 and procs a 150 damage lifetap.  Alot of Paladins on Xegony from 40- low 50's are still using GHOULBANE, which Abashi admited if your using it 40+ that you wernt doing the damage you should be doing.  <BR>
<BR>
ok i think i said my fair share of ranting =p<BR>

